{"lemma":"عارِيَةٌ","slug":"عارِيَةٌ","root":"ع.ر.#","root_slug":"ع-ر-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ر-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30985"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30985","headword_ar":"عَارِيَّةٌ","root":"Ewr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K) and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAriyapN","text_ar":"عَارِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without teshdeed, (Msb, K,) when used in poetry, (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArapN","text_ar":"عَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is taken by persons by turns;"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA tadaAwaluwhu","text_ar":"مَا تَدَاوَلُوهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumo","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [generally meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a loan:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act of lending;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"putting one in possession of the use of a thing without anything given in exchange:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT, and Kull p. 262:) the returning of the thing thus termed is obligatory, when the thing itself remains in existence; and if it has perished, then one must be responsible for its value, accord. to Esh-Sháfi'ee, but not accord. to Aboo-Haneefeh: (TA:) pl. [of the first]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaAriY~u","text_ar":"عَوَارِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) and [of the second]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaArK","text_ar":"عَوَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, K.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA@loEawaAriY~u qaSaArN A^ano turado \n                      \n                     \n                        A_in~amaA A^anofusunaA EaAriy~apN"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Our souls are only a loan: and the end of loans is their being given back:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turado","text_ar":"تُرَدْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turad~a","text_ar":"تُرَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAriy~apN","text_ar":"عَارِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEoliy~apN","text_ar":"فَعْلِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": Az says that it is a rel. n. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArapN","text_ar":"عَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iEaArapN","text_ar":"اـِعَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, * Msb:) Lth says that what is thus called is so called because it is a disgrace ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAr","text_ar":"عار"},{"kind":"text","text":") to him who demands it; and J says the like; and some say that it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAra Alfarasu","text_ar":"عَارَ الفَرَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, “ the horse went away from his master: ” but both these assertions are erroneous; since"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAry~p","text_ar":"عاريّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"belongs to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewr","text_ar":"عور"},{"kind":"text","text":", for the Arabs say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo yataEaAwaruwna AlEawaAriY~a","text_ar":"هُمْ يَتَعَاوَرُونَ العَوَارِىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they lend"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loans"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one to another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArN","text_ar":"عَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAra Alfarasu","text_ar":"عَارَ الفَرَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"belong to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyr","text_ar":"عير"},{"kind":"text","text":": therefore the correct assertion is that of Az. (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","O","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}